<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>i3 FAQ - Individual question feed</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/questions/</link><description>Frequently asked questions and answers about the i3 window manager</description><atom:link href="http://faq.i3wm.org/feeds/question/5408/" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Copyright i3, 2012</copyright><lastBuildDate>Fri, 30 Jan 2015 09:19:33 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>move cursor to another screen</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5408/move-cursor-to-another-screen/</link><description>Is it possible to move cursor to an adjacent display ? 

In awesome and dwm I had a binding `$mod+&lt;` and `$mod+&gt;`, which moved cursor to the left/right screen. I know in i3 I can just focus workspace that is active on an external monitor but then I need to know what number it is. </description><pubDate>Fri, 30 Jan 2015 08:59:19 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5408/move-cursor-to-another-screen/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by lasers for &lt;p&gt;Is it possible to move cursor to an adjacent display ? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In awesome and dwm I had a binding &lt;code&gt;$mod+&amp;lt;&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;$mod+&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;, which moved cursor to the left/right screen. I know in i3 I can just focus workspace that is active on an external monitor but then I need to know what number it is. &lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5408/move-cursor-to-another-screen/?answer=5409#post-id-5409</link><description>    focus output &lt;&lt;left|right|down|up&gt;|output&gt;

